## Design for scale

- **Design for scale.** Prefer patterns that stay sound as usage and domains grow: respect existing layering in **`fitness-backend`** (domain modules vs `app/core`, routers vs services vs repositories), avoid unbounded queries and accidental N+1 or O(n²) paths where lists and aggregations are involved, and use pagination, batching, caching, and indexing in line with how the backend already handles reads and writes. When a shortcut trades clarity or performance for speed, call that out and fix it before it becomes load-bearing.

Aligned with [Documentation/Fitness Platform - System Design.md](../../Documentation/Fitness%20Platform%20-%20System%20Design.md) and [fitness-backend/documentation/Backend Design Spec.md](../../fitness-backend/documentation/Backend%20Design%20Spec.md).

---

## Security

- **Security.** Never commit secrets, API keys, or production credentials; keep `.env*`, private keys, and service tokens out of repos, screenshots, and chat. On the **API**, verify identity on every protected route (JWT / Supabase auth per the phased roadmap; local debug paths only where explicitly documented), scope every read/write to the authenticated principal (and by `user_id` when multi-tenancy is in effect), validate and bound inputs at boundaries, and return errors that do not leak stack traces, tokens, or other users’ data. On **clients** (future iOS / web), use TLS to the API, follow the project auth flows once implemented, and avoid logging PII, tokens, or full payloads.

Aligned with [Documentation/Fitness Platform - System Design.md](../../Documentation/Fitness%20Platform%20-%20System%20Design.md) and [fitness-backend/documentation/Backend Design Spec.md](../../fitness-backend/documentation/Backend%20Design%20Spec.md).

