## Implementation (pair programming / learning)

Use this when extending **`fitness-backend`**, adding **workers** or **domains**, or integrating **future clients** (iOS offline-first, web SPA per system design). It complements **Change communication** above.

### High-level architecture (for learning)

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  subgraph clients [Clients]
    iOS[iOS SwiftUI + SwiftData]
    Web[Web SPA future]
  end
  subgraph api [fitness-backend]
    FastAPI[FastAPI]
    Domains[Domain modules]
    DB[(PostgreSQL)]
    Redis[(Redis)]
    Workers[Workers / tasks]
    FastAPI --> Domains
    Domains --> DB
    FastAPI --> Redis
    Workers --> Redis
    Workers --> DB
  end
  iOS -->|HTTPS REST JSON| FastAPI
  Web -->|HTTPS REST JSON| FastAPI
```

- **Backend:** Modular monolith under `fitness-backend/app/domains/*` with routers, services, repositories; shared infrastructure in `app/core`.
- **MVP product:** Post-workout logging, sync, and AI-related pipelines per specs — see global and backend docs for current phase scope.
- **Clients:** iOS-first, offline-first with eventual consistency; web is in the architecture doc as a future client — keep API contracts stable and documented when both consume the same service.

### Learning checkpoints (pair-programming pauses)

Backend and platform work is tracked in **`Documentation/Plans/`** (e.g. [Backend Implementation Plans.md](../../Documentation/Plans/Backend%20Implementation%20Plans.md)). When the user asks to **pause after each phase or section** of a plan, work in **small batches**, stop after each agreed checkpoint, and explain **what** changed, **why** it matters, and **how to verify** (`make lint`, `make test`, `make dev`, etc., from `fitness-backend/`).

- **Default:** A plain **“execute”** may ship work in **larger batches**; still give high-level summaries per **Change communication** above.
- **Checkpoint mode:** When the user says **“use the plan checkpoints”**, **“pause after each phase”**, or similar, follow the active plan file and **stop** after each checkpoint until they say **continue**.
- **Retrospective:** They can ask for a walkthrough **without new code** to map plan sections to files already in the repo.

If a plan file differs from this rule, **follow the plan** and update this rule when the checkpoint scheme changes.

